"OrientDB can be found at this website: http://orientdb.org/. 
It is an open-source noSQL/non-relational database. OrientDB uses a hybrid data model, and can use document, key-value, and graph models. 
It is a local or client/server hosting model. 
Java can access OrientDB and Python using native drivers, which allows applications to connect and interact with the database. 
Java uses the OrientDB Java driver and Python uses the Py0rient driver. 
This information can be found at the OrientDB website and this source: http://orientdb.org/docs/3.0.x/misc/Overview.html."
